    "created_at": "2015-10-09T23:33:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-09T23:33:32Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Sure.  I don't want to need to know the order of the indices in the MultiIndex.  E.g.\n\n``` python\nmi = MultiIndex((('a', 'b'), ('A', 'B')), ((0, 0), (0, 1), (1, 0), (1, 1)), names=('foo', 'bar'))\ndf = Series(..., index = mi)\n```\n\nI want to be able to write something like\n\n``` python\ndf[mi(foo = 'a', bar = 'b')]\n```\n\nor similar to get the correct Series elements.\n\nMaybe this functionality already exists in MultiIndex, but I didn't see it and decided to subclass.\n"
  },
